Hurricane Gilbert brought more than 24 hours of heavy rain to Monterrey and  Matamoros, Mexico, causing severe flooding and deaths.
In the industrial city of  Monterrey, at least 10 police officers on a rescue mission were swept away by the Santa  Catarina River.
Several buses full of evacuees were overturned by high water in  Matamoros.
Heavy rainfall, flooding, mudslides, and tornadoes are accompanying the  remnants of Gilbert.
Power outages are continuing and many remain in shelters.
The  hurricane has killed at least 109 people and relief operations to bring emergency food,  water, and medical supplies are continuing across the Yucatan Peninsula. 
